                  <unitdatestructured label="creation" unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <datesingle standarddate="1933">1933</datesingle>
                  </unitdatestructured>
                  <container altrender="/repositories/11/top_containers/398139"
                             id="aspace_68870139be42b99e8670785d3cc34315_c1"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">8</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_46e48c0f4be355e285aeb2c27b29e570">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Scrapbook containing photographs, maps, clippings, postcards, brochures, programs, and other ephemera documenting Helen Solberg Fowler's time as a student at Omnibus College in the summer of 1933.  As part of her studies, Fowler participated in a traveling caravan of students and teachers, which included field trips in Wyoming, Illinois, Massachusetts, New York, New Jersey, Washington, D.C., Virginia, and Kentucky.</p>
               </scopecontent>
